A recent study by al- Basrah Centre of Culture has shown that almost half of all married couples in Iraq are in physical pain due to disunity. Unfortunately, these high rates of marital discord are not unique to Iraqi society. Divorce and spousal suffering are also increasingly found in other Arabic nations such as Lebanon and Jordan. While personal freedom and women’s rights are a symbolizes a hallmark of democracy, in reality Americans are more likely to experience divorce, spousal abuse and child abuse.

The new study found that marital discord in Iraq is greatly due to the poor media and technology which does not help towards loading the negative traditional opinions of the new Iraqi generation. Read more..
